The MVD of Russia is proposing to tighten the law in relation to owners of civilian weapons.
It is the reaction of the government authorities to recent events: the impetus was the shooting at weddings, which went without victims, and the massacre prepared by the Moscow lawyer Dmitry Vinogradov, as a result of which seven people died.
Police want to ban the carrying of dangerous weapons in public places and raise the age at which a license to carry weapons can be obtained from 18 to 21.
