An open letter has appeared in the network, the authors of which - representatives of various social shooting organizations - demand the rejection of the "senseless tightening" of the law.
The percentage of hooliganism with registered weapons is minimal, Vasily Lesnikov, a lawyer and criminologist, said in an interview with the BBC's Russian bureau.
According to statistics from the Ministry of Internal Affairs, in the six months of 2012, 142 crimes were committed using firearms registered by the authorities of the Ministry of Internal Affairs, while for the same period a total of 1168 thousand crimes were committed.
The authors of the open letter are convinced that tightening legislation on civilian weapons will not force the offender to switch to the "black" market.
According to them, any weapon at a low price can currently be found in Moscow.
At present, the Ministry of the Interior claims that the situation with the spread of illegal weapons is under control.
Suppliers: from factories to officers
The "black" arms market is supplied through several channels.
There are five main channels, says retired colonel Victor Baranets, who worked for ten years at the Ministry of Education and the General Staff.
