The court, headed by Carlos Díaz Chávez Morineau, has just filed a lawsuit against the National Banking Commission and the Securities and Exchange Commission, accusing it of obstructing justice.
In its view, the Authority systematically refused to report to the Prosecutor General's Office of the Republic on a transaction carried out by that entrepreneur in which he withdrew 198 million pesos from IXE Bank from fideicommissum F/589 on behalf of Mexican Aviation.
The funds were most likely directed towards buying shares in the Professional Hotel Management (Administradora Profesional de Hoteles).
As is well known, Azcárraga Andrade is the majority shareholder of the Posadas hotel chain.
Siege of Dragon Mart
A group of domestic and foreign environmentalists, academics, businessmen and ordinary citizens gathered at the Universidad de Caribe over the weekend and approved the creation of an association to prevent the opening of China's Dragon Mart in Kankun.
We are talking, as is known, about a huge trade and distribution center with products from the "country with a big wall" focused on Mexico, Central America and the Caribbean, which at the bottom would include a residential zone for employees from 150 companies.
