End of the ACTA affair
The Senate's request, which the government ignored and which demanded clarification on the conditions and circumstances under which the Mexican ambassador signed the Anti-Counterfeiting Trade Agreement, known by its acronym ACTA, in Japan, has lost its relevance, according to the Mexican Institute of Industrial Property (Instituto Mexicano de la Propiedad Industrial).
As is well known, this happened despite the fact that the Senate itself ruled out the possibility of considering it a threat to freedom of expression on social networks.
Homex in the long term
In an effort to pay off long-term debts and not affect short-term ones, the development company Homex is marketing investment certificates worth 500 million pesos.
