Héctor "Hetin" Reyes: "Basketball was my life"
Basketball globetrotter Héctor "Hetin" Reyes has been associated with this indoor sport for more than 60 years and has traveled the world thanks to it.
Few people in Puerto Rico have as many memories of local basketball history as Héctor "Hetin" Reyes has.
Before a stroke confined him to a wheelchair in 2008, Reyes had been passionate about the sport for more than 60 years, whether as a junior player, a BSN player in the national basketball league, owner and coach of the Vaqueros de Bayamón National Basketball League, and president of the Puerto Rico Basketball Federation.
"I've held many roles in basketball throughout my life, including several at the same time, like when I was president of the BSN National League, general manager of the national team and chairman of the federation in the '90s," Reyes recalled while visiting reporters from the newspaper Primera Hora at his home in Bayamón, where he has lived for more than 50 years with Isabel, his faithful wife.
"Basketball was my life."
